		</nav><main><h1>School Closure Information</h1>
<span style="font-size:22px"><strong>Click Here: <a href="https://documentcloud.adobe.com/link/track?uri=urn%3Aaaid%3Ascds%3AUS%3Ac1ec93cd-fffe-49e6-ac7c-a54051ccae1d">Emergency School Closure Q&amp;As</a></strong></span><br><br><strong>FLATHEAD COUNTY SUPERINTENDENT OF SCHOOLS</strong><br><br>
1.  All schools will close if the highway department declares “Emergency Travel Only” on <span style="background-color:#ffff00">state highways</span>. The County Superintendent’s Office will activate the phone tree as soon as the alert is received.<br><br>
2.  All schools will close if the <span style="background-color:#ffff00">county</span> declares “Emergency Travel Only” (Bigfork to be determined). The County Superintendent’s Office will activate the phone tree as soon as the alert is received.<br><br>
3.  High schools will make a <u>final decision</u> about closure (when the above 1 &amp; 2 are NOT in effect) and call The County Superintendent by 6:00 a.m. The County Superintendent will e-mail two radio stations with the information—KOFI and Bee Broadcasting. Telephone notification to the two radio stations will be an alternative. (Bigfork excluded.)<br><br>
4.  <u>Rural elementary districts</u> close in conjunction with the appropriate high school. If a decision is made to close <span style="background-color:#ffff00">regardless of the high schools</span>, call The County Superintendent . The County Superintendent will e-mail the information to the two radio stations—KOFI and Bee Broadcasting. Telephone notification to the two radio stations will be an alternative.<br><br>
5.  High school districts call The County Superintendent if schools remain open but bus routes are cancelled. Information will be e-mailed to the two radio stations.<br><br>
6.  <u>Rural elementary districts</u> call The County Superintendent with bus route cancellations. Information will be e-mailed to the two radio stations.<br><br>
7.  Schools may decide to have a delayed start if they feel weather would permit doing so. <br><br></main><footer>
